[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797326882&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797326882&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


 Could someone save me some wheel re-invention?  I have seen postings
 recently about wildcarding MX records exterior to a nameserver's
 primary domain, but I can't get interior wildcard MX records to work...

 I am primary for buffalo.edu.  I want to send MX info via wildcard records
 for
   *.arch.buffalo.edu
   *.geog.buffalo.edu

 and others.  So I want records like-

 *.arch.buffalo.edu.    IN    MX   0  romulus.arch.buffalo.edu.
 *.geog.buffalo.edu.    IN    MX   0  iroquois.geog.buffalo.edu.

 Can I do this?  Has someone done this?  Can you send me your data files?
 thanks
 JoAnn

